 hints if u can provide me with it<br>thanks in advance <br>=) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ugothicchaos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>gothic chaos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/17/02 4:44:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=715.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: needing help</span><hr size=1> Well, to begin with, if your planning on your story being a manga I suggest a script format. It will be easier to plan out scenes that way.<br><br>Now, for how to write the story. You can plan out diffrent segments of the story,like concerning time flow, or locations. Normally when writing a book(at least in my experience)it is a good idea to write it all the way through, but for manga you would want to have a general overview of the story(timeline and summary)and begin writing chapter by chapter, making sure to leave something hanging at the end of each.<br><br>Now, for what makes a good story.....It really all depends on what sort of genre your writing in. For say, romance its best to have an element of drama, and in most cases tragedy. Now, if you were doing something concerning horror, suspense, surprise and a twisted point of view(concerning the world, or bad guy..) are all elements that are best included.<br><br>The best thing though, when trying to write a good story, its best to plan things out carefully before actually writing and to try and avoid stereotypes. Who wants to read about another good-doing, all around perfect hero type when there could be so many more interesting characters?<br><br>If you need any more suggestions, please ask, and I hope things go well with your endevors. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=l